This paper discusses the potential harmful impacts of advances in machine learning, particularly in the creation of synthetic media. It focuses on the question of publication and release processes around such research, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses strategies for mitigating research risks, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the manipulation of images and videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
